BSC-BPM
===================================================================
Warning! BSC-BPM is not stable. Check the releases page for the latest stable versions.


Update: 4.2.1
===================================================================
In the most recent update, I made it so that if you install a package that has an 'install.sh' file, 
you can compile it and it will run the .sh file.

Updating is now 90% done! It does require a separate package though. To install run 'bpm install update-util' and then 'bpm --compile update-util'.
Then, you can run 'bpm-update'

Manual update

compile: 'bpm --compile <package>'

Upcoming Features
===================================================================
MHS-FS Filesystem support

────────────────────────────────────┐
Compiling, Installing, and Updating.│
────────────────────────────────────┘

Installation
===================================================================
git clone https://github.com/BizzyPythonBear/BearShellC-BPM BSC-BPM
cd BSC-BPM
sudo make install
bpm --help

Updating
===================================================================
sudo make update

Compiling (If you decided to make your own changes to the code)
===================================================================
sudo make compile
